  "content": "d: var(--surface-2); }\n.role-dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; }\n.graph-controls { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; padding: 0.5rem; align-items: center; }\n.depth-control { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; }\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 7: Manual verification**\n\nStart the dashboard dev server and verify:\n- Cluster view loads as before (initial state)\n- Clicking a cluster transitions to entry-level view\n- Clicking an entry opens the reader panel\n- Hover highlights connected nodes, fades others\n- Reader panel shows content, metadata badges, neighbor cards\n- Clicking a neighbor card navigates graph + updates reader\n- Filters narrow visible nodes\n- Depth slider works\n\n- [ ] **Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace\ngit add tools/corvia-dashboard/src/\ngit commit -m \"feat(dashboard): split-panel graphed document reader with entry-level interaction\"\n```\n\n---\n",
